{
  "texts": [
    "This need for domain-specific, robust data complicates design and training.",
    "A robot operating on a factory floor requires carefully calibrated cameras, LiDAR, or haptic sensors.",
    "At the same time, an autonomous drone might rely on GPS, inertial measurement units, and computer vision to navigate.",
    "Each sensor stream demands real-time processing and reliable fusion techniques to provide a coherent view of the world.",
    "Consequently, computing power in AI 3.0 shifts toward distributed and edge computing architectures."
  ]
}